Object.assign(TRANSLATIONS.en, {
  "faq.meta.description": "Nexa FAQ — Clear, practical answers about platform, implementation, integrations, security, and pricing.",
  "faq.meta.ogTitle": "Nexa FAQ — Everything you need to know before deciding",
  "faq.meta.ogDescription": "How long does activation take? Does Nexa replace my ERP? What hardware do I need? Answered directly.",
  "faq.meta.title": "Nexa FAQ — Everything you need to know before deciding",
  "faq.hero.badge": "Frequently asked questions",
  "faq.hero.title": "Everything you need to know<br>before deciding.",
  "faq.hero.copy": "Short, direct answers to the questions operators ask most when evaluating Nexa. You don't need a demo to understand how it works.",
  "faq.hero.sidecardAria": "FAQ topic summary",
  "faq.hero.sidecardTitle": "What you'll find",
  "faq.hero.topic1": "<span>Getting started</span><strong>Scope and fit</strong>",
  "faq.hero.topic2": "<span>The platform</span><strong>Modules and flows</strong>",
  "faq.hero.topic3": "<span>Implementation</span><strong>Timelines and team</strong>",
  "faq.hero.topic4": "<span>Security & data</span><strong>Ownership and availability</strong>",
  "faq.hero.topic5": "<span>Pricing & access</span><strong>Commercial model</strong>",
  "faq.sidebar.aria": "FAQ navigation",
  "faq.sidebar.start": "Getting started",
  "faq.sidebar.platform": "The platform",
  "faq.sidebar.implementation": "Implementation",
  "faq.sidebar.security": "Security & data",
  "faq.sidebar.pricing": "Pricing & access",
  "faq.q1.q": "What exactly is Nexa?",
  "faq.q1.a": "<p>Nexa is the central operating system that replaces spreadsheets and WhatsApp messages in charcuterie, cheese, and dairy flows.</p><p>Instead of fragmented tools, it gives your team one reliable screen to manage inventory, monitor temperature, and coordinate dispatch without guessing.</p>",
  "faq.q2.q": "What type of company is Nexa designed for?",
  "faq.q2.a": "<p>Nexa is built for three types of operators:</p><p><strong>Importers & wholesalers</strong> — handle large volumes of cheese, charcuterie, and dairy with intake control and bulk inventory mapping.</p><p><strong>Distributors</strong> — run last-mile for specialty orders with a B2B portal, FEFO dispatch, and digital proof of delivery.</p><p><strong>Cold storage operators</strong> — manage multi-chamber facilities, aging rooms, and dairy stock with planned monitoring, alerts, and food safety records.</p><p>If you manage refrigerated food at commercial scale, Nexa applies to your operation.</p>",
  "faq.q3.q": "Does Nexa replace my ERP?",
  "faq.q3.a": "<p><strong>No: Nexa is not an ERP.</strong> It operates alongside your existing ERP, not in its place.</p><p>Think of Nexa as the operational execution layer: it handles catalog, inventory visibility, order processing, and planned thermal control. Your ERP keeps handling finance, accounting, and procurement.</p><p>Bidirectional ERP integration via REST API is on our roadmap. In the current MVP, data is exported manually in standard formats.</p>",
  "faq.q4.q": "What do I need to have ready before starting?",
  "faq.q4.a": "<p>Very little. You don't need a sophisticated digital infrastructure to start with Nexa.</p><p>The minimum is: a list of your SKUs, a basic idea of your distribution nodes or cold rooms, and access to the devices your team already uses.</p><p>If you already have IoT sensors, we review compatibility as a roadmap integration. In TB1 it is not presented as implemented hardware.</p>",
  "faq.q5.q": "What are the five modules and what does each do?",
  "faq.q5.a": "<p><strong>Product data</strong> — your full product list with SKU codes, temperature ranges, shelf life windows, and prices.</p><p><strong>Operational inventory</strong> — visible stock levels in the MVP, with FEFO and alerts demonstrated using test data.</p><p><strong>B2B portal</strong> — a self-service interface for distributors, retailers, and buying teams. They see catalog, place orders, and track dispatch without calling.</p><p><strong>Delivery evidence</strong> — drivers can register signature, photo, and planned temperature evidence as part of the product flow.</p><p><strong>Traceability</strong> — batch movement is modeled for later backend and persistence integration.</p>",
  "faq.q6.q": "Can I use some modules without activating all five?",
  "faq.q6.a": "<p>Yes. Modules can be activated progressively. Many operations start with catalog and inventory, then add the B2B portal, then mobile telemetry.</p><p>All five modules share one data layer, so adding a new one doesn't require heavy migrations or reconfigurations.</p>",
  "faq.q7.q": "How does FEFO (First Expired, First Out) work in practice?",
  "faq.q7.a": "<p>When a B2B order comes in, Nexa shows the FEFO rule for prioritizing the batch with the closest expiry date, not the newest batch.</p><p>This avoids treating manual picking as enough control. Full automation depends on later backend and persistence.</p>",
  "faq.q8.q": "What level of detail does the traceability module capture?",
  "faq.q8.a": "<p>Every batch receives a chain-of-custody model: origin, producer, production date, transfers, storage, chamber assignment, and final delivery.</p><p>PDF, GPS, and automations are roadmap items after the TB1 MVP.</p>",
  "faq.q9.q": "How long does it take to go live?",
  "faq.q9.a": "<p><strong>The web MVP can be reviewed quickly because it uses demo data.</strong> Full implementation, including sensors, ERP, backend, and training, stays on the later roadmap.</p><p>Scope is separated by phase so future integrations are not presented as delivered in TB1.</p>",
  "faq.q10.q": "What hardware is compatible with Nexa?",
  "faq.q10.a": "<p>Nexa is designed to be hardware-agnostic. Temperature sensor integration via REST or MQTT is on the roadmap; compatibility with specific brands is confirmed before implementation.</p><p>You do not need to replace existing equipment to review the TB1 MVP.</p>",
  "faq.q11.q": "Does my team need technical training to use Nexa?",
  "faq.q11.a": "<p><strong>No.</strong> The interface was designed for warehouse managers, drivers, and dispatch teams, not IT departments. Drivers use their own phone: open a link, take a photo, register delivery, and tap 'deliver'.</p><p>Hands-on training is planned by phase. Temperature integrations stay separate from the TB1 MVP.</p>",
  "faq.q12.q": "Does Nexa support multi-node or multi-facility operations?",
  "faq.q12.a": "<p>Yes. Nexa is built for multi-node operations. You can manage multiple warehouses, distribution hubs, and cold rooms from one account, with each node visible separately on the dashboard.</p><p>Stock is controlled independently per node, but everything consolidates into one inventory view. Thermal alerts remain segmented by chamber or facility.</p>",
  "faq.q13.q": "Who owns my operational data?",
  "faq.q13.a": "<p><strong>Your organization.</strong> Your inventory, customer relationships, order history, and temperature logs belong to your operation. Nexa processes them only to run the platform.</p><p>You can export everything in standard formats at any time. If you stop using Nexa, your data leaves with you.</p>",
  "faq.q14.q": "How is my data protected?",
  "faq.q14.a": "<p><strong>Your data is continuously backed up and kept separate from other customers.</strong> Everything travels encrypted so only your authorized stakeholders can see inventory and orders.</p><p>For technical and compliance teams: we maintain immutable 7-year logs and redundant infrastructure so a localized physical failure doesn't cut your dispatch capacity.</p>",
  "faq.q15.q": "What happens if Nexa goes down?",
  "faq.q15.a": "<p>Nexa operates with a 99.9% uptime SLA. The platform is designed to degrade gracefully: if a network fails, mobile telemetry keeps logging locally and syncs when connectivity returns.</p><p>Critical operations like delivery confirmation keep working offline. The dashboard shows cached data and clearly indicates any sync delay.</p>",
  "faq.q16.q": "How is Nexa priced?",
  "faq.q16.a": "<p><strong>We quote based on your operational volume</strong>: we measure number of nodes and implementation scale. We don't charge per seat or per driver, so you don't need to restrict access to save money.</p><p>When you explain your operation, we send a closed proposal within two business days. No surprise costs, no hidden integrations.</p>",
  "faq.q17.q": "Can I see a demo before committing?",
  "faq.q17.a": "<p>Yes. We run live guided walkthroughs tailored to your operation — not a generic demo. Tell us what you manage and we'll show you exactly how Nexa solves that flow.</p><p><a href=\"company.html#contact\">Use the contact form</a> to request a session. We respond within one business day.</p>",
  "faq.q18.q": "What do the first 30 days after demo review include?",
  "faq.q18.a": "<p><strong>You have a direct line to our team, not a ticket system.</strong> We monitor the first real dispatches, confirm thermal data syncs correctly, verify FEFO is working, and fix any configuration issues that surface in operation.</p><p>After 30 days, your team operates independently. Support doesn't disappear: you still reach a real person by email or phone.</p>",
  "faq.cta.badge": "Still have questions?",
  "faq.cta.title": "We answer directly.",
  "faq.cta.copy": "Tell us about your operation and we'll respond with specifics. No sales script, no pressure.",
  "faq.cta.note": "Next step",
  "faq.cta.meta": "Use the contact channel if you need a direct answer instead of another product page.",
  "faq.cta.primary": "Contact us",
  "faq.cta.secondary": "Explore the platform"
});

